<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>FlipperZero on The Expat Tech</title><link>https://zdevilinside.github.io/TheExpatTech/tags/flipperzero/</link><description>Recent content in FlipperZero on The Expat Tech</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Mon, 24 Nov 2025 14:35:49 -0600</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://zdevilinside.github.io/TheExpatTech/tags/flipperzero/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Resetting a Flipper Zero</title><link>https://zdevilinside.github.io/TheExpatTech/posts/tech-tips/flipper-zero-reset/</link><pubDate>Mon, 24 Nov 2025 14:35:49 -0600</pubDate><guid>https://zdevilinside.github.io/TheExpatTech/posts/tech-tips/flipper-zero-reset/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Do you have a Flipper Zero that you forgot the pin to? It is actually quite easy to reset.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
 &lt;thead&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/thead&gt;
 &lt;tbody&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;1. Remove the microSD card from the device.&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;img
 class="lazyload"
 src="https://zdevilinside.github.io/TheExpatTech/svg/loading.min.svg"
 data-src="./image4.png"
 data-srcset="./image4.png, ./image4.png 1.5x, ./image4.png 2x"
 data-sizes="auto"
 alt="./image4.png"
 title="image 4" /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;2. Hold the UP and BACK buttons for 30 seconds.&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;img
 class="lazyload"
 src="https://zdevilinside.github.io/TheExpatTech/svg/loading.min.svg"
 data-src="./image2.jpg"
 data-srcset="./image2.jpg, ./image2.jpg 1.5x, ./image2.jpg 2x"
 data-sizes="auto"
 alt="./image2.jpg"
 title="image 2" /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;3. When it asks you if you want to reset, push the right button to confirm that you want to reset it.&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;:)&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If that doesn&amp;rsquo;t work, you will need to run qFlipper.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>